{title: Lonely Is Another State}
{artist: John Anderson}
{composer: Written by Ervan James Parker and John David Anderson}

[G]There’s nothing I feel stronger than the need to travel on
Never knowing where I’m going or [C]how long I’ll be gone
There’s [Am]no need makin’ promises [C]cause promises are something I can’t [D7]keep
[G]These highways are old memories I’ve traveled many times
And there’s no destination on the [C]road map in my mind
And [Am]somethings always calling me  [C]to a place I hope I’ll [D7]find
[C]And this old road gets kinda [G]lonesome
[B7]And sometimes I get lonesome [Em]too
[C]And I know it won’t last for[G]ever
[A7]Lonely is another state and I’m just passing [D7]through
