I had a good job in a factory and a [C]house outside of town
But I [Am]felt the need to be somewhere [C]I’d never been be[D7]fore
And if I don’t see tomorrow I’m thankful for today
And all the things I’ve ever seen [C]while traveling on my way
Every [Am]change in times and scenery and [C]the friends I’ve met along the [D7]way
[C]And this old road gets kinda [G]lonesome
